Package: arronax
Architecture: all
X-Python-Version: >= 2.7
Depends: arronax-base, arronax-nautilus,
Description: Nautilus plugin to create and modify application starters.
 Arronax is a plugin for the Gnome file manager Nautilus. It lets you create 
 and modify application starters (*.desktop files).
 .
 This is a virtual package that depends on the standalone version and the 
 Nautilus plugin of Arronax


Package: arronax-base
Architecture: all
X-Python-Version: >= 2.7
Depends:  ${python:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}, gir1.2-glib-2.0,  gir1.2-gtk-3.0, python-gobject (>= 2.90), gir1.2-gdkpixbuf-2.0, python-pkg-resources, python-xdg
Description: Create and modify application starters.
 Arronax lets you create and modify starters (*.desktop files) for aplications,
 files and URIs
 .
 This package contains the standalone version of Arronax


Package: arronax-nautilus
Architecture: all
X-Python-Version: >= 2.7
Depends: ${python:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}, arronax-base, nautilus (>= 3.4.1), python-nautilus,
Description: Create and modify application starters.
 Arronax lets you create and modify starters (*.desktop files) for applications,
 files and URIs.
 .
 This package contains the Nautilus plugin for Arronax. It adds a 
 "Create starter" menu item to the Desktop's context menu and to the file 
 context menu in Nautilus
